{"type":"message","id":"e690325e","parentId":"1a46e92d","timestamp":"2026-07-06T15:19:38.968Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The file is very long. Let me focus on the key parts I need to examine:\n\n1. For the WASM灰色问题: I need to look at the page switching logic, especially how `divPlugin` is handled when switching between console and replay pages. I already saw the CSS change in index.html:\n```css\n.page { position:absolute; top:0; left:0; width:100%; visibility:hidden; opacity:0; pointer-events:none; }\n.page.active { position:relative; visibility:visible; opacity:1; pointer-events:auto; }\n```\n\nBut the key issue is: when switching from replay back to console, does the WASM player restart? Let me look at the initNav click handler more carefully.\n\nFrom the index.html initNav code:\n```javascript\nif (btn.getAttribute('data-page') === 'console') {\n    refreshPtzDeviceList();\n    // 自动播放:已登录但未播放时开始预览\n    if (WasmPlayer && WasmPlayer.loggedIn && !WasmPlayer.playing) {\n        var ch = WasmPlayer.channel || 1;\n        var st = window._currentStreamType || 3;\n        wasmStartRealPlay(ch, st, true);\n    }\n}\n```\n\nSo when switching to console, if logged in but not playing, it tries to restart preview. But the issue is the WASM container `divPlugin` might lose its rendering context.\n\nAlso important: the `moveVideoToConsole()` function moves `divPlugin` back to console. But looking at the nav handler:\n```javascript\nif (btn.getAttribute('data-page') === 'advanced') {\n    moveVideoToAdvanced();\n    initAdvSidebar();\n} else if (btn.getAttribute('data-page') === 'console') {\n    moveVideoToConsole();\n}\n```\n\nWait, this only calls `moveVideoToConsole()` when going to console, but it doesn't call it when going to replay. So when going to replay, `divPlugin` stays in its current position (console or advanced). That's actually good - it means the container isn't moved.\n\nBut the problem is: when the page switches, the `divPlugin` is inside the console page div. When console page is `visibility:hidden`, the container is hidden. Even though it's not `display:none` (which was the previous fix), the visibility:hidden might still cause issues with WASM rendering.\n\nActually wait, let me re-read the CSS:\n```css\n.page { position:absolute; top:0; left:0; width:100%; visibility:hidden; opacity:0; pointer-events:none; }\n.page.active { position:relative; visibility:visible; opacity:1; pointer-events:auto; }\n```\n\nSo when console page is not active, it has `visibility:hidden; opacity:0`. The container is hidden but still in DOM with position:absolute. This should preserve GPU context... but maybe the WASM SDK is pausing/stopping when the container is hidden?\n\nLet me look at the replay page more carefully. When the user clicks on a video in the replay page, it opens a modal with a `<video>` element. That shouldn't affect the WASM player.\n\nBut the user says \"回到主控台，WASM依然是灰色\" - so after viewing replay and going back to console, the WASM player is gray. The initNav code tries to restart preview if `!WasmPlayer.playing`, but maybe `WasmPlayer.playing` is still true (the WASM didn't actually stop, it just looks gray).\n\nLet me now check the file serving endpoints for the thumbnail and video serving.\n\nLet me also check the router.py for the file-related endpoints.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"现在让我检查 `router.py` 中与文件相关的端点（缩略图、服务、列表、信息）："},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_3a763024bf0d433f8cd570b1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Select-String -Path astrohub\\src\\api\\router.py -Pattern \"(thumb|files/serve|files/list|files/info|files/delete|files/open|record)\" -CaseSensitive:$false | Select-Object -First 40 | ForEach-Object { $_.LineNumber.ToString() + \": \" + $_.Line.Trim() }","timeout":10,"workdir":"C:\\Users\\admin\\.openclaw\\agents\\dev-factory"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"HP","model":"glm-5.2","usage":{"input":57904,"output":887,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":58791,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1783351150563,"responseId":"cht000d26ff@dx19f3803259529bb503"}}
